'''meism''' ''n.'' '''meisms (pl.)''' [ < me and -ism . ]

1. ''Colloquialism''. A saying that is particular to one's self

Note: Rush Limbaugh claimed coinage during his radio show on EIB Network of March 23, 2005.  Evidence of the word's use exists on Usenet almost two decades before Rush passed it off as his own:
'...another example of why folks are concerned about the "meism" attitude that seems to prevail when twanks get behind the wheel...'

2. A model of learning: needs-driven, life-centered, auto-apropriated learning.  Learning that takes into account individual cognitive environment: self esteem, emotionality, quality of life. Learning as self actualisation and transformation.



